Ask HN: Is IT the canary for the next recession?
text:
Hey all,

Almost daily we get headlines for company X laying off Y people, Y being usually large-ish.

Is the IT industry bracing for a rapidly coming recession? Or is it just a trend that’s being utilized to cut excess personnel off as a generally good business practice, but without doomsday clouds on the horizon?

title: “We be of one blood, ye and I” – advice to founders
Ask HN: Does YC fund startups that don't plan to have a >$5M valuation?
text:
I have an idea for a service I want to build, that I think I'll be able to sell to big tech for $2M-20M (not sure how much exactly yet)

Based on YC's "standard deal" it seems like they're investing in companies which have plans to exit for much larger figures (their minimum investment is 500K, with 125K of that for 7% of the company)

TBH, I don't really understand how the MFN terms of the remaining 375K works, but since it's a relatively simple service I expect to be able to build and grow over the course of a year, I don't expect to need more than 125K.

Does YC invest in companies that don't have "massive" potential?

title: Show HN: Stream realtime example data to your InfluxDB
text:
Hi! I built a tiny app to write example data into an empty InfluxDB database. It gives you temperature and CO2 data from 10 houses from different places around the world.

Just add some temporary credentials and the data starts streaming in realtime.

Let me know what you think about it!

P.S. Not 100% clear on the page, but to be secure, create a new bucket and token only for this app.

GPT-3 API Down
text:
I have been receiving large numbers of API errors from GPT-3 - the PAID service - stating that the server is overloaded with other requests. My application is effectively broken.

It would appear that they must have allocated more capacity to ChatGPT, as that is also complaining about capacity issues

Does anyone have any experience with other commercial offerings for an LLM service that may be comparable to davinci-003? It seems I cant trust OpenAI to keep a pay-for service operational when they are too busy trying to build PR through their "free" tool.
